		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Charleston</placeName>&#44; <date>August 10. 1859</date>.</p>
				<p rend="align(center)"><addressee>Rev. Is. Leeser</addressee>&#8212;<placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir&#8212;<sic>Inclosed</sic> I send you the continuation<lb/> of &#8220;A Gala Day&#8221; &#38;c.  For the II Article on &#8220;A Board of<lb/> Deputies&#8221; you must await another week&#59; I am too<lb/> weak to do more now&#44; for I have just risen from the<lb/> sick&#45;bed&#44; having again&#8212;as every summer&#8212;been visited<lb/> by&#8212;inflammatory dysentery.  Indeed&#33;  Only the consideration<lb/> not to have any interception in the first&#45;named essay<lb/> could induce me to take up my pen this week&#59; for even<lb/> the mechanical work of translating affects me severely.<lb/>  I find out more and more every summer&#44; that the climate<lb/> of <placeName>Charleston</placeName> is undermining my constitution&#44; and I begin<lb/> to think seriously upon a permanent change&#44; especially<lb/> as I cannot hope even for leave of absence&#44; as long as<lb/> <del>the present</del> our Board of Trustees is constituted as it is<lb/> at present.  So be not astonished if you should perhaps<lb/> sooner than you might expect&#8212;hear of my resignation.<lb/>  The <placeName>Charleston</placeName> climate is certainly none for <hi rend="underline">students</hi>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">How is <persName>Mars</persName>&#63;  Why have you not reputed the result<lb/> &#38;c. &#38;c. of his first sermon&#63;  What is in the wind&#63;  Did<lb/> he not &#8220;<hi rend="underline">take</hi>&#8221;&#63;  I have my <hi rend="underline">private</hi> reasons to ask<lb/> these questions.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Have you seen and read <persName>Dr Kayserling&#39;s</persName> work&#58; &#8220;Sephardim.<lb/> Romanische Poesicen der Juden in Spanien&#8221;&#63;  For many years&#44; no<lb/> work by a Jew has given me more delight than this Book.<lb/>  I intend to write of course for the <hi rend="underline">Occident</hi>&#44; if welcome to its</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>editor&#8212;a very lengthy review&#44; with <add>&#63;</add> extracts upon the<lb/> book.  Such a book is apt&#44; and ought to create national<lb/> pride in the hearts of all Jews.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I cannot write more now&#8212;so <hi rend="underline">Vale</hi><add>&#63;</add></p>
			<p rend="indent(6)">Yours</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">M Mayer</persName></p>
			
